result.adr_address: 15 Gough St, Central, Hong Kong
result.name: Gough's on Gough

reviews.text:
Came there to drink coffee and found by mistake one of the best cocktails bars in the city.
The atmosphere and design of the place is amazing.
You are treated like a king, no less.
The bartender was really nice and helpful, doing his best to make us feel like home and making us the best cocktail for us.
The atmosphere is relaxing and you can spend a whole evening there without noticing.

A very nice restaurant to experience excellent fine dining with your families and friends. Dishes, glasses and cutlery are beautiful. Gough's on Gough gives you a comfort and relaxing mood with dimmed light. A 4-course French dinner (May of French festival) made us a fruitful evening. It is a must for me and my family to come again. (Thank you for the surprises to my loved ones birthday.)

It is absolutely an amazing restaurant, good vibe, attentive service, especially the food - best beef wellington (medium rare), and the sticky toffee pudding, OMG, it tastes so so so so super good!! Super tasty meal. Not cheap, but worth a try, and several try!

Fantastic food and service.  The oysters are a must try.  Doesn't feel like a kid-friendly restaurant but it probably wasn't meant to be one.  The decor alone is worth a visit though. The red-bellied piranhas at the front is a nice touch.  Tip: they have a private room at the back that seats 4.
Nice atmosphere. Food start to serve at 7pm. Didn’t have a chance to try yet. Come so early. But definitely guarantee to come for photo. It’s awesome place for photo shooting.
